    <section class="col-xl-6 mb-5">
        <h2>Client's Assessment Needs</h2>
        <p>The clients wanted to better understand how their services were being used. To accomplish this they tasked us with implementing a user assessment on their website. We had to ensure the placement of this assessment was not invasive to the current job submission user flow, especially because our clients were concerned with survey fatigue as the job submission process already required a lot of clicking. </p>
    </section>
</section>

<h2>Creating a Prototype</h2>
    <p class="mb-5">I was tasked with creating a prototype for our addition to the client’s website and identified two areas within the job submission process that could contain the assessment. I utilized Figma, allowing us to visualize how the form would appear in each area. We then started development after meeting with the client to confirm which variant of the prototype they preferred. 
    </p>
